5000|$|Electronic Logging Devices (ELDs) is {{the most}} recent term to define an {{electronic}} device {{that is capable of}} recording a driver's <b>driving</b> <b>hours</b> and duty status automatically. In order to be considered an ELD, the device must meet specific technology requirements and be included on the Federal Motor Carrier Safety Administration’s (FMCSA) registration site.|$|R
